60ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
61
62#define KEY_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D','S','T','K')
63#define CTX_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D','S','T','C')
64
65#define VALID_KEY(x) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(x, KEY_MAGIC)
66#define VALID_CTX(x) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(x, CTX_MAGIC)
67
68/***
69 *** Types
70 ***/
71
72typedef struct dst_func dst_func_t;
73
74typedef struct dst_hmac_key dst_hmac_key_t;
75
76/*%
77 * Indicate whether a DST context will be used for signing
78 * or for verification
79 */
80typedef enum { DO_SIGN, DO_VERIFY } dst_use_t;
81
82/*% DST Key Structure */
83struct dst_key {
84 unsigned int magic;
85 isc_refcount_t refs;
86 dns_name_t * key_name; /*%< name of the key */
87 unsigned int key_size; /*%< size of the key in bits */
88 unsigned int key_proto; /*%< protocols this key is used for */
89 unsigned int key_alg; /*%< algorithm of the key */
90 uint32_t key_flags; /*%< flags of the public key */
91 uint16_t key_id; /*%< identifier of the key */
92 uint16_t key_rid; /*%< identifier of the key when
93 revoked */
94 uint16_t key_bits; /*%< hmac digest bits */
95 dns_rdataclass_t key_class; /*%< class of the key record */
96 dns_ttl_t key_ttl; /*%< default/initial dnskey ttl */
97 isc_mem_t *mctx; /*%< memory context */
98 char *engine; /*%< engine name (HSM) */
99 char *label; /*%< engine label (HSM) */
100 union {
101 void *generic;
102 gss_ctx_id_t gssctx;
103 DH *dh;
104#if USE_OPENSSL
105 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
106#endif
107#if USE_PKCS11
108 pk11_object_t *pkey;
109#endif
110 dst_hmac_key_t *hmac_key;
111 } keydata; /*%< pointer to key in crypto pkg fmt */
112
113 isc_stdtime_t times[DST_MAX_TIMES + 1]; /*%< timing metadata */
114 bool timeset[DST_MAX_TIMES + 1]; /*%< data set? */
115 isc_stdtime_t nums[DST_MAX_NUMERIC + 1]; /*%< numeric metadata */
116 bool numset[DST_MAX_NUMERIC + 1]; /*%< data set? */
117 bool inactive; /*%< private key not present as it is
118 inactive */
119 bool external; /*%< external key */
120
121 int fmt_major; /*%< private key format, major version */
122 int fmt_minor; /*%< private key format, minor version */
123
124 dst_func_t * func; /*%< crypto package specific functions */
125 isc_buffer_t *key_tkeytoken; /*%< TKEY token data */
126};
127
128struct dst_context {
129 unsigned int magic;
130 dst_use_t use;
131 dst_key_t *key;
132 isc_mem_t *mctx;
133 isc_logcategory_t *category;
134 union {
135 void *generic;
136 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *gssctx;
137 isc_hmac_t *hmac_ctx;
138 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx;
139#if USE_PKCS11
140 pk11_context_t *pk11_ctx;
141#endif
142 } ctxdata;
143};
144
145struct dst_func {
146 /*
147 * Context functions
148 */
149 isc_result_t (*createctx)(dst_key_t *key, dst_context_t *dctx);
150 isc_result_t (*createctx2)(dst_key_t *key, int maxbits,
151 dst_context_t *dctx);
152 void (*destroyctx)(dst_context_t *dctx);
153 isc_result_t (*adddata)(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *data);
154
155 /*
156 * Key operations
157 */
158 isc_result_t (*sign)(dst_context_t *dctx, isc_buffer_t *sig);
159 isc_result_t (*verify)(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *sig);
160 isc_result_t (*verify2)(dst_context_t *dctx, int maxbits,
161 const isc_region_t *sig);
162 isc_result_t (*computesecret)(const dst_key_t *pub,
163 const dst_key_t *priv,
164 isc_buffer_t *secret);
165 bool (*compare)(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2);
166 bool (*paramcompare)(const dst_key_t *key1,
167 const dst_key_t *key2);
168 isc_result_t (*generate)(dst_key_t *key, int parms,
169 void (*callback)(int));
170 bool (*isprivate)(const dst_key_t *key);
171 void (*destroy)(dst_key_t *key);
172
173 /* conversion functions */
174 isc_result_t (*todns)(const dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data);
175 isc_result_t (*fromdns)(dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data);
176 isc_result_t (*tofile)(const dst_key_t *key, const char *directory);
177 isc_result_t (*parse)(dst_key_t *key,
178 isc_lex_t *lexer,
179 dst_key_t *pub);
180
181 /* cleanup */
182 void (*cleanup)(void);
183
184 isc_result_t (*fromlabel)(dst_key_t *key, const char *engine,
185 const char *label, const char *pin);
186 isc_result_t (*dump)(dst_key_t *key, isc_mem_t *mctx, char **buffer,
187 int *length);
188 isc_result_t (*restore)(dst_key_t *key, const char *keystr);
189};
190
191/*%
192 * Initializers
193 */
194isc_result_t dst__openssl_init(isc_mem_t *, const char *engine);
195#define dst__pkcs11_init pk11_initialize
196
197isc_result_t dst__hmacmd5_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
198isc_result_t dst__hmacsha1_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
199isc_result_t dst__hmacsha224_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
200isc_result_t dst__hmacsha256_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
201isc_result_t dst__hmacsha384_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
202isc_result_t dst__hmacsha512_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
203isc_result_t dst__openssldh_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
204#if USE_OPENSSL
205isc_result_t dst__opensslrsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp,
206 unsigned char algorithm);
207isc_result_t dst__opensslecdsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
208#if HAVE_OPENSSL_ED25519 || HAVE_OPENSSL_ED448
209isc_result_t dst__openssleddsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
210#endif /* HAVE_OPENSSL_ED25519 || HAVE_OPENSSL_ED448 */
211#endif /* USE_OPENSSL */
212#if USE_PKCS11
213isc_result_t dst__pkcs11rsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
214isc_result_t dst__pkcs11dsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
215isc_result_t dst__pkcs11ecdsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
216#if defined(HAVE_PKCS11_ED25519) || defined(HAVE_PKCS11_ED448)
217isc_result_t dst__pkcs11eddsa_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
218#endif
219#endif /* USE_PKCS11 */
220#ifdef GSSAPI
221isc_result_t dst__gssapi_init(struct dst_func **funcp);
222#endif /* GSSAPI */
223
224/*%
225 * Destructors
226 */
227void dst__openssl_destroy(void);
228#define dst__pkcs11_destroy pk11_finalize
229
230/*%
231 * Memory allocators using the DST memory pool.
232 */
233void * dst__mem_alloc(size_t size);
234void dst__mem_free(void *ptr);
235void * dst__mem_realloc(void *ptr, size_t size);
236
